Remove vendor folder

This should not be tracked for following reasons:
1 - These files are pulled in by composer anyway.
2 - It loads checkouts up with unneeded files.
3 - As vendor dir was committed in August 2014, files it contains
are notably out of date.
4 - After you do a composer install or update, git status gets
flooded with masses of changed files in vendor/ - the signal of
your changes gets lost in the noise of the changed vendor/ files.
Add vendor dir and compiled bootstrap to .gitignore

Tests with sqlite in-memory

Update Install controller test to reflect use of Laravel DB gubbins

Hook up in-memory DB for testing.

This diff renders database as used in automated test suite
independent of configured production database connection - you can
freely run tests without affecting your production database.

I tested the above by turning off my local MySQL server - test suite
did not complain and ran exactly as it had before I turned my local
server off.

I am aiming to enable more aggressive and comprehensive automated
testing, at unit, integration and functional levels.  For example,
assuming Laravel's functionality is up to it, it now should be possible
to write a functional test that creates a new user (possibly with
some problems) and verify that the new user gets created cleanly or
not at all..
Upgrade php unit and clean up mock objects in tests
Fix stock test cases

Merge pull request #37 from csouth/master

Fixing removal of $ from config values

Fixing error when dates are not provided.

When dates are not provided this was throwing an error (because DateTime::createFromFormat returns false if the date supplied is not valid). This change will just null out any dates that aren't provided.

Fixing removal of $ from config values

This fixes the remove of dollar signs in config values (for example passwords). Before the install would fail if your password had a $ in it because what was returned did not match what was passed in (Example: If your password is Pa$sw0rd it would write Pasw0rd to the config, thus triggering the error on line 52.
